MOSCOW June 15. 2023 (Saba) â€“ Russian Deputy Foreign Minister Sergei Ryabkov has announced that the number of countries wishing to join BRICS group, which currently includes Russia, China, India, Brazil and South Africa, is increasing. Deputy Ryabkov confirmed that the number of countries wishing to join BRICS has reached nearly twenty, adding that the list of countries wishing to join the group is growing, and the number of countries interested in joining this group is close to twenty countries. He noted that this reflects the growing and already very important role of the BRICS group in the international arena as a group of like-minded parties.